Project Overview
This is a 2D interactive game where players control an aircraft to catch falling objects (apples). It was developed to demonstrate GUI design and hardware-software integration using a Raspberry Pi.

How to Run / Demonstration
Due to the hardware-specific nature of this project (Raspberry Pi and Joystick) and the legacy environment it was built on, it may be difficult to compile on modern systems. To provide a clear overview of the results, a demonstration video is included in the repository. For technical review, please refer to the source code for implementation details.

Technologies Used
Language: C++

Framework: Qt

Hardware: Raspberry Pi, Joystick

Personal Contributions
As the lead programmer and designer, I was responsible for the majority of the project's development, including:

System Architecture: Designed and implemented the overall game framework and logic.

Core Game Mechanics: Developed the game loop, timing system, and scoring logic.

Problem Solving: Engineered a custom, coordinate-based collision detection system to overcome library limitations and ensure responsive gameplay.

Hardware Integration: Programmed the interface to sync physical joystick inputs with software movement.
